The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Vertex Deletion problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields. The paper presents tight lower bounds on the running time of the problem under different assumptions and restrictions, which suggests that the problem is of interest to researchers in theoretical computer science. The categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are all relevant to the study of graph algorithms and complexity, and are therefore likely categories for this paper.
